		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64569403"><p>Apparently <i>systemd</i> development doesn't adhere to the "principle of least astonishment" which I've always tried to adhere to.</p><p>Admittedly I've not <i>always</i> successfully followed this principle but fortunately the resulting failures have (to my knowledge) resulted in "astonishment" such as <i>"Why did this set of options give me a syntax error?"</i> rather than <i>"Where did my data go?"</i>.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64569403">
